==Latin==

===Etymology===
from the Latin phrase 'status quo [[ante]] [[bellum]]', meaning the way things were before the war.

===Noun===
'''[[status]] [[quo]]'''

# The [[state]] of [[thing]]s; used in English to refer to the [[way]] things are, as opposed to the way they could be; the [[existing]] state of [[affairs]]. 

